.instInhabitedConfig.default\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">instInhabitedConfig</span>.<span class=\"name\">default</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.instInhabitedConfig.default","kind":"def","line":223,"name":"Lean.Grind.instInhabitedConfig.default","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L223-L223"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.maxSuggestions\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">maxSuggestions</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum number of library suggestions to use. If `none`, uses the default limit.\nOnly relevant when `suggestions` is `true`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.maxSuggestions","kind":"def","line":222,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.maxSuggestions","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L222-L222"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.reducible\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">reducible</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true`, use reducible transparency when trying to close goals.\nIn this setting, only declarations marked with `@[reducible]` are unfolded during\ndefinitional equality tests.\n\nThis option does not affect the canonicalizer or how theorem patterns are internalized;\nreducible declarations are always unfolded in those contexts.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.reducible","kind":"def","line":217,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.reducible","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L217-L217"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.funCC\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">funCC</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true`, it enables **function-valued congruence closure**.\n`grind` treats equalities of partially applied functions as first-class equalities\nand propagates them through further applications.\nGiven an application `f a₁ a₂ … aₙ`, when `funCC := true` *and* function equality is enabled for `f`,\n`grind` generates and tracks equalities for all partial applications:\n- `f a₁`\n- `f a₁ a₂`\n- `…`\n- `f a₁ a₂ … aₙ`\n\nThis allows equalities such as `f a₁ = g` to propagate to\n`f a₁ a₂ = g a₂`.\n\n**When is function equality enabled for a symbol?**\nFunction equality is automatically enabled in the following cases:\n1. **`f` is not a constant.** (For example, a lambda expression, a local variable, or a function parameter.)\n2. **`f` is a structure field projection**, *provided the structure is not a `class`.*\n3. **`f` is a constant marked with the attribute:** `@[grind funCC]`\n\nIf none of the above conditions apply, function equality is disabled for `f`, and congruence\nclosure behaves almost like it does in SMT solvers for first-order logic.\nHere is an example, `grind` can solve when `funCC := true`\n```\nexample (a b : Nat) (g : Nat → Nat) (f : Nat → Nat → Nat) (h : f a = g) :\n  f a b = g b := by\ngrind\n```\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.funCC","kind":"def","line":208,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.funCC","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L208-L208"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.revert\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">revert</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true`, it reverts all hypotheses during the preprocessing step,\nand then reintroduces them while simplifying and applying eager `cases`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.revert","kind":"def","line":178,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.revert","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L178-L178"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.useSorry\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">useSorry</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `trace := true`, uses `sorry` to close unsolved branches.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.useSorry","kind":"def","line":173,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.useSorry","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L173-L173"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.detailed\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">detailed</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Minimum number of instantiations to trigger detailed report in `#grind_lint`.\nRemark: this option is only relevant for the `#grind_lint` command.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.detailed","kind":"def","line":169,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.detailed","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L169-L169"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.min\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">min</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Minimum number of instantiations to trigger summary report in `#grind_lint`.\nRemark: this option is only relevant for the `#grind_lint` command.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.min","kind":"def","line":164,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.min","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L164-L164"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.order\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">order</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true` (default: `true`), enables the procedure for handling orders that implement\nat least `Std.IsPreorder`\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.order","kind":"def","line":159,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.order","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L159-L159"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.inj\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">inj</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true` (default: `true`), enables the procedure for handling injective functions.\nIn this mode, `grind` takes into account theorems such as:\n```\n@[grind inj] theorem double_inj : Function.Injective double\n```\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.inj","kind":"def","line":154,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.inj","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L154-L154"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.abstractProof\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">abstractProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true` (default: `true`), automatically creates an auxiliary theorem to store the proof.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.abstractProof","kind":"def","line":146,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.abstractProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L146-L146"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.exp\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">exp</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum exponent eagerly evaluated while computing bounds for `ToInt` and\nthe characteristic of a ring.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.exp","kind":"def","line":142,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.exp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L142-L142"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.acSteps\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">acSteps</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum number of steps performed by the `ac` solver.\nA step is counted whenever one AC equation is used to simplify another.\nFor example, given `ma x z = w` and `max x (max y z) = x`, the first can be\nused to simplify the second to `max w y = x`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.acSteps","kind":"def","line":137,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.acSteps","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L137-L137"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.ac\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">ac</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true` (default: `true`), uses procedure for handling associative (and commutative) operators.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.ac","kind":"def","line":130,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.ac","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L130-L130"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.lia\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">lia</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true` (default: `true`), uses procedure for handling linear integer arithmetic for `Int` and `Nat`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.lia","kind":"def","line":126,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.lia","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L126-L126"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.linarith\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">linarith</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true` (default: `true`), uses procedure for handling linear arithmetic for `IntModule`, and\n`CommRing`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.linarith","kind":"def","line":122,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.linarith","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L122-L122"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.ringSteps\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">ringSteps</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum number of steps performed by the `ring` solver.\nA step is counted whenever one polynomial is used to simplify another,\nweighted by the number of terms in the resulting polynomial.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.ringSteps","kind":"def","line":117,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.ringSteps","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L117-L117"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.ring\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">ring</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true` (default: `true`), uses procedure for handling equalities over commutative rings.\nThis solver also support commutative semirings, fields, and normalizer non-commutative rings and\nsemirings.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.ring","kind":"def","line":111,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.ring","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L111-L111"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.zeta\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">zeta</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When `true` (default: `true`), performs zeta reduction of let expressions during normalization.\nThat is, `let x := v; e[x]` reduces to `e[v]`. See also `zetaDelta`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.zeta","kind":"def","line":105,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.zeta","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L105-L105"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.zetaDelta\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">zetaDelta</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"When set to `true` (default: `true`), local definitions are unfolded during normalization and internalization.\nIn other words, given a local context with an entry `x : t := e`, the free variable `x` is reduced to `e`.\nNote that this behavior is also available in `simp`, but there its default is `false` because `simp` is not\nalways used as a terminal tactic, and it important to preserve the abstractions introduced by users.\nAdditionally, in `grind` we observed that `zetaDelta` is particularly important when combined with function induction.\nIn such scenarios, the same let-expressions can be introduced by function induction and also by unfolding the\ncorresponding definition. We want to avoid a situation in which `zetaDelta` is not applied to let-declarations\nintroduced by function induction while `zeta` unfolds the definition, causing a mismatch.\nFinally, note that congruence closure is less effective on terms containing many binders such as\n`lambda` and `let` expressions.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.zetaDelta","kind":"def","line":100,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.zetaDelta","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L100-L100"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.mbtc\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">mbtc</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `mbtc` is `true`, `grind` will use model-based theory combination for creating new case splits.\nSee paper \"Model-based Theory Combination\" for details.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.mbtc","kind":"def","line":87,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.mbtc","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L87-L87"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.qlia\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">qlia</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `qlia` is `true`, `grind` may generate counterexamples for integer constraints\nusing rational numbers, and ignoring divisibility constraints.\nThis approach is cheaper but incomplete. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.qlia","kind":"def","line":82,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.qlia","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L82-L82"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.clean\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">clean</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `clean` is `true`, `grind` uses `expose_names` and only generates accessible names. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.clean","kind":"def","line":77,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.clean","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L77-L77"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.verbose\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">verbose</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `verbose` is `false`, additional diagnostics information is not collected. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.verbose","kind":"def","line":75,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.verbose","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L75-L75"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.lookahead\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">lookahead</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"TODO ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.lookahead","kind":"def","line":73,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.lookahead","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L73-L73"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.funext\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">funext</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `funext` is `true`, `grind` creates new opportunities for applying function extensionality by case-splitting\non equalities between lambda expressions.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.funext","kind":"def","line":71,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.funext","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L71-L71"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.etaStruct\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">etaStruct</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `etaStruct` is `true`, then for each term `t : S` such that `S` is a structure,\nand is tagged with `[grind ext]`, `grind` adds the equation `t = ⟨t.1, ..., t.n⟩`\nwhich holds by reflexivity. Moreover, the extensionality theorem for `S` is not used.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.etaStruct","kind":"def","line":66,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.etaStruct","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L66-L66"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.extAll\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">extAll</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `extAll` is `true`, `grind` uses any extensionality theorems available in the environment. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.extAll","kind":"def","line":60,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.extAll","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L60-L60"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.ext\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">ext</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `ext` is `true`, `grind` uses extensionality theorems that have been marked with `[grind ext]`. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.ext","kind":"def","line":58,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.ext","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L58-L58"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.canonHeartbeats\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">canonHeartbeats</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum number of heartbeats (in thousands) the canonicalizer can spend per definitional equality test. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.canonHeartbeats","kind":"def","line":56,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.canonHeartbeats","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L56-L56"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.splitImp\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">splitImp</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `splitImp` is `true`, then given an implication `p → q` or `(h : p) → q h`, `grind` splits on `p`\nif the implication is true. Otherwise, it will split only if `p` is an arithmetic predicate.\n","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.splitImp","kind":"def","line":54,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.splitImp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L54-L54"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.splitIndPred\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">splitIndPred</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `splitIndPred` is `true`, `grind` performs case-splitting on inductive predicates.\nOtherwise, it performs case-splitting only on types marked with `[grind cases]` attribute. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.splitIndPred","kind":"def","line":49,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.splitIndPred","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L49-L49"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.splitIte\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">splitIte</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `splitIte` is `true`, `grind` performs case-splitting on `if-then-else` expressions during the search. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.splitIte","kind":"def","line":45,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.splitIte","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L45-L45"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.splitMatch\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">splitMatch</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `splitMatch` is `true`, `grind` performs case-splitting on `match`-expressions during the search. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.splitMatch","kind":"def","line":43,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.splitMatch","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L43-L43"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.matchEqs\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">matchEqs</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `matchEqs` is `true`, `grind` uses `match`-equations as E-matching theorems. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.matchEqs","kind":"def","line":41,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.matchEqs","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L41-L41"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.instances\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">instances</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum number of theorem instances generated using E-matching in a proof search tree branch. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.instances","kind":"def","line":39,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.instances","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L39-L39"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.gen\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">gen</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum term generation.\nThe input goal terms have generation 0. When we instantiate a theorem using a term from generation `n`,\nthe new terms have generation `n+1`. Thus, this parameter limits the length of an instantiation chain. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.gen","kind":"def","line":37,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.gen","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L37-L37"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.ematch\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">ematch</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum number of E-matching (aka heuristic theorem instantiation) rounds before each case split. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.ematch","kind":"def","line":32,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.ematch","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L32-L32"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.splits\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">splits</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum number of case-splits in a proof search branch. It does not include splits performed during normalization. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.splits","kind":"def","line":30,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.splits","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L30-L30"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.locals\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">locals</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `locals` is `true`, `grind` will add all definitions from the current file. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.locals","kind":"def","line":28,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.locals","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L28-L28"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.suggestions\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">suggestions</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `suggestions` is `true`, `grind` will invoke the currently configured library suggestion engine on the current goal,\nand add attempt to use the resulting suggestions as additional parameters to the `grind` tactic. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.suggestions","kind":"def","line":26,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.suggestions","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L26-L26"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.lax\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">lax</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `lax` is `true`, `grind` will silently ignore any parameters referring to non-existent theorems\nor for which no patterns can be generated. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.lax","kind":"def","line":23,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.lax","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3dc1a088b6d2d8eafe25a7cd7ec7b58d731bd7cc/src/Init/Grind/Config.lean#L23-L23"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.markInstances\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">markInstances</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `markInstances` is `true`, E-matching proofs are marked with instance IDs\nfor precise tracking of which theorems appear in the final proof. ","docLink":"./Init/Grind/Config.html#Lean.Grind.Config.markInstances","kind":"def","line":20,"name":"Lean.Grind.Config.markInstances","sou